<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 9:40PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Colder with Light Snow...
A new cold front is advancing southward through Central Montana
this evening, producing a broad area of light snow and lowering
temperatures back below zero. Expect visibility reduced to around
1/2 mile in snow. Northerly winds have increased with the passing
front, producing wind chill values of 15 to 25 degrees below zero.
Use caution if traveling, and carry a vehicle safety kit including
extra warm clothing. Snow will continue off and on at times
overnight while temperatures continued to lower into the teens
below zero.</description>
